We will be woring in Windows and using the VSCode IDE

Install python3

Create a project folder eg. FlaskIntroduction

Open VSCode IDE

Hit Ctrl ~ to open a terminal

Install virtualenv from terminal
	pip install virtualenv

Type virtualenv env at the terminal
	A folder 'env' will be created in your project

Activate the virtual environment
	env\Scripts\activate.bat (be wary of backslashes) (btw .bat is optional)
	The command prompt will be prefixed with (env)

NOTE: You can deactivate the environment by typing:
	env\Scripts\deactivate.bat

PROCEED TO INSTALL REQUIREMENTS

Install Flask
	pip install flask flask-sqlalchemy

Create the simplest of all app 'app.py'

From the terminal run the app:
	python app.py
	An app server will start running at http://127.0.0.1:5000
	Hold down Ctrl and click on the link, a web page will be loaded in browser
